licy specified by policyId.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eIf the return code is not OK, the errorMessage field of the TagPolicyResponseDTO may contain additional details describing the cause of the error.","examples":["https://192.168.1.1/securetrack/api/tagpolicy/policies/policyId || {\n\t\t\"status\": \"OK\",\n\t\t\"policy_name\": \"myPolicyName\"\n}"],"position":"4","type":"TagPolicyResponseDTO","nickname":"delete","produces":["application/json"],"consumes":["application/json"],"parameters":[{"name":"context","description":"Delete policy of the specified domain ID","required":false,"type":"integer","format":"int32","paramType":"query","allowMultiple":false,"allowableValues":"","hidden":false},{"name":"policyId","description":"cloud tag policy id","required":false,"type":"string","paramType":"path","allowMultiple":false,"allowableValues":"","hidden":false}],"responseMessages":[{"code":200,"message":"Successful"},{"code":400,"message":"Invalid request"},{"code":403,"message":"Insufficient user permissions"},{"code":404,"message":"Resource not found"}]},{"baseURL":"/securetrack/api","method":"PATCH","summary":"Modify a cloud tag policy","notes":"Partially modify a cloud tag policy by stating the modified attributes. Providing requirements replaces the entire list.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003eSpecifying an empty requirement list is not permitted. Modify some attributes of the cloud tag policy specified by policyID with the attributes provided. If one or more \"requirement\" objects is provided, the exsiting \"requirement\" objects will be deleted and replaced with the new objetcs. Specifying an empty requirement list is not permitted.If the return code is not OK, the errorMessage field of the TagPolicyResponseDTO may contain additional details describing the cause of the error.","examples":["https://{ip}/securetrack/api/tagpolicy/policies/policyId |{\n\t\"policy_name\": \"myPolicyName\",\n\t\"requirements\": [\n\t\t{\n\t\t\t\"requirement_type\": \"mandatory_tags\",\n\t\t